"'''A Time to Mourn, a Time to Dance: Oola's Tale'''" is a short story by [[Kathy Tyers]] found in the ''[[Tales from Jabba's Palace]]'' anthology which was published by [[Bantam Spectra]] [[December]] [[1995]]. It details the backstory of the dancing girl [[Oola/Legends|Oola]].

==Plot summary==
[[Oola/Legends|Oola]] and her companion dancer [[Sienn'rha|Sienn]] are taken from [[Ryloth/Legends|Ryloth]] by [[Bib Fortuna/Legends|Bib Fortuna]] to [[Tatooine/Legends|Tatooine]]. [[Jabba Desilijic Tiure/Legends|Jabba's]] [[Majordomo/Legends|majordomo]] promises them soft living at the famous [[Jabba's Palace/Legends|Hutt's palace]]. However, upon arrival, Oola is dismayed to discover that Tatooine is a horridly hot and [[Desert/Legends|desert]] [[Planet/Legends|planet]], a discovery alleviated only by her dreams of lush luxury at Jabba's palace. During a brief stay in [[Mos Eisley/Legends|Mos Eisley]], Fortuna leaves the two dancers momentarily, during which absence they encounter [[Luke Skywalker/Legends|Luke Skywalker]], who warns them against serving Jabba. Oola's friend flees with Skywalker, but Oola herself remains, jealously thinking she can thus ensure Jabba's patronage for herself alone. However, once at the palace, chained to the loathsome [[Gangster/Legends|gangster]], Oola learns how mistaken she is and regrets her choices, but has some solace in knowing Sienn has been spared this fate. Fortunately for her, hope is renewed when she learns from [[C-3PO/Legends|C-3PO]] that Luke Skywalker is planning a rescue mission for another [[Prisoner/Legends|prisoner]] at the palace. Heartened anew, Oola accepts Jabba's demand for her to dance, vowing to herself that this shall be her greatest dance yet - not realizing it will be her last.

==Continuity==
[[Sienn'rha|Sienn]] made a brief appearance in ''[[X-Wing: The Krytos Trap]]'' ([[1996]]) set three [[Standard year/Legends|years]] after her liberation from [[Jabba's Palace/Legends|Jabba's palace]].<ref name="TERC" />

